sentences.english: I mentioned that this happened in New Jersey, right?
sentences.chinese: 我提起的這事情發生在新澤西，對吧？

sentences.english: USS New Jersey BB-62 after the 1968 modernization.
sentences.chinese: 1968年經過現代化改裝後的新澤西號戰列艦。

sentences.english: Stranahan, a graduate student at Princeton University in New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 是新澤西州普林斯頓大學的畢業生。

sentences.english: The Liberal Democrat from New Jersey died Monday. He was 89.
sentences.chinese: 勞坦柏是新澤西的自由民主黨成員，享年89歲。

sentences.english: There is golf-ball-size hail in New Jersey today.
sentences.chinese: 新澤西州今日下起高爾夫球大小的冰雹。

sentences.english: Let us have a look at New Jersey's pre-eminent University Town.
sentences.chinese: 讓我們看看新澤西出類拔萃的大學城。

sentences.english: First Presbyterian Church in Pitman , New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 第一長老教會在必新澤西。

sentences.english: During the English Civil War the Channel Isle of Jersey remained loyal to the Crown and gave sanctuary to the King.
sentences.chinese: 在英國內戰海峽澤西島仍忠於官方和庇護了國王。

sentences.english: A little further south, look at these New Jersey homes.
sentences.chinese: 往南去，我們來看看新澤西州的家庭。

sentences.english: Actually I did grow up in Edison, New Jersey.
sentences.chinese: 我是在新澤西州的愛迪生市長大的。

sentences.english: bury an urn in Elizabeth New Jersey, B'nai Israel Cemetery
sentences.chinese: 把骨灰甕埋在新澤西州伊麗莎伯布萊猶太人墓地。

sentences.english: One New Jersey man decided to paint the exterior of his house to save money.
sentences.chinese: 新澤西有位仁兄爲了省錢，決定自己粉刷屋子的外牆。

sentences.english: Its members reside and work in New Jersey and New York, possessing rich experience in choral singing.
sentences.chinese: 其成員廣散於紐約及新澤西各地，均具豐富合唱經驗。

sentences.english: The Los Angeles to New Jersey footrace did not sound quite so appealing.
sentences.chinese: 洛杉磯到新澤西的長跑，叫起來就不那麼響亮了。

sentences.english: Mr. Lee: Hmmm … a photo I. D. I have my New Jersey driver's license. Is that ok?
sentences.chinese: 有照片的證件。我有新澤西的駕駛執照，可以嗎？
